Vasquez, Drake, hold your fire, goddamn it!

752
01:15:12,940 --> 01:15:16,865
Apone, are you copying me? I want you to lay down suppressing fire...

753
01:15:16,940 --> 01:15:19,560
with the incinerators and fall back by squads to the A.P.C.

754
01:15:19,580 --> 01:15:21,947
- Over. - Say again, all after "incinerator."

755
01:15:22,020 --> 01:15:26,708
I said I want you to lay down a suppressing fire with the incinerators and fall back...

756
01:15:26,820 --> 01:15:29,391
by squads to the A.P.C. Over.

757
01:15:30,300 --> 01:15:31,347
Hey!

758
01:15:33,300 --> 01:15:35,701
- Sarge! Sarge! - Apone.

759
01:15:35,780 --> 01:15:38,226
- Talk to me. Apone? - Copy! Copy!

760
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:40,587
- Talk to me, Apone. - He's gone!

761
01:15:42,260 --> 01:15:44,627
- Get them out of there! - Shut up!

762
01:15:44,740 --> 01:15:46,630
- Do it now! - Shut up!

763
01:15:46,780 --> 01:15:49,756
- Hicks, whoever's left, get the hell out of there... Goddamn it! - Just shut up!

764
01:15:49,780 --> 01:15:54,183
- It's coming out of the goddamn walls! - Where's Apone? Where's Apone?

765
01:15:54,260 --> 01:15:56,581
The sarge is gone! Let's get the fuck out of here!

766
01:15:56,660 --> 01:16:00,460
Let's move it! Let's go, marine!

767
01:16:00,540 --> 01:16:03,623
Hudson? Vasquez?

768
01:16:03,740 --> 01:16:06,823
- Hudson, look out! - Get it!

769
01:16:07,940 --> 01:16:09,942
Watch it!

770
01:16:10,020 --> 01:16:12,421
- Hicks. - Come on. Behind you! Fall back!

771
01:16:12,540 --> 01:16:16,130
- I told them to fall back. I told them to fall back. - Fall back, goddamn it, now!

772
01:16:16,140 --> 01:16:17,983
- They're cut off! - Hudson, move your ass!

773
01:16:18,140 --> 01:16:20,029
- Do something! - Let's go, marine!

774
01:16:20,100 --> 01:16:22,068
Fuck!

775
01:16:22,180 --> 01:16:25,150
- Come on. Keep moving, baby. - Hold on, Newt.

776
01:16:30,940 --> 01:16:34,183
Ripley, what the hell are you doing?

777
01:16:40,100 --> 01:16:41,829
Turn around!

778
01:16:45,180 --> 01:16:47,581
That's an order!

779
01:16:51,060 --> 01:16:54,542
- Get off me, damn it! - Goddamn it, that's an order!

780
01:16:54,620 --> 01:16:57,351
You had your chance, Gorman.

781
01:17:08,660 --> 01:17:10,583
Come on!

782
01:17:30,140 --> 01:17:32,791
Come on. Let's move it!

783
01:17:32,860 --> 01:17:35,227
Come on! Let's go! Let's go!

784
01:17:35,300 --> 01:17:38,747
It's blocked, man. We gotta go around!

785
01:17:38,820 --> 01:17:43,621
- Open the door! Hicks! - Drake, we are leaving!

786
01:17:43,700 --> 01:17:45,702
Get them, man!

787
01:17:46,580 --> 01:17:49,186
Run for it!

788
01:17:50,260 --> 01:17:52,706
Shit!

789
01:17:55,460 --> 01:17:58,748
- Go! Go! - Come on, man! Come on!

790
01:18:06,820 --> 01:18:10,711
Drake, come on!

791
01:18:13,220 --> 01:18:15,461
No!

792
01:18:17,540 --> 01:18:20,384
- Fire in the hole! - He's gone!

793
01:18:20,460 --> 01:18:22,349
Put it out! Put it out! Go! Go!

794
01:18:22,420 --> 01:18:26,141
- Come on. Put it out! - Drake's coming, man!

795
01:18:26,260 --> 01:18:29,230
- Drake! No, he's not! - He's gone!

796
01:18:30,620 --> 01:18:32,588
Forget him! He's gone!

797
01:18:38,420 --> 01:18:40,343
They're in the goddamn door!

798
01:18:43,780 --> 01:18:46,511
Eat this!

799
01:18:46,580 --> 01:18:49,663
Ripley!

800
01:18:49,740 --> 01:18:52,061
Go, go, go!

801
01:19:54,860 --> 01:19:56,749
It's all right! We're clear!

802
01:19:56,860 --> 01:19:59,261
Ripley, you've blown the transaxle!

803
01:19:59,340 --> 01:20:01,263
You're just grinding metal!

804
01:20:01,340 --> 01:20:03,547
Come on, ease down.

805
01:20:03,660 --> 01:20:05,708
Ease down.

806
01:20:05,780 --> 01:20:09,546
Ease down. Ease down.

807
01:20:21,220 --> 01:20:23,461
You okay?

808
01:20:24,820 --> 01:20:26,868
- I'm all right. - Hudson.

809
01:20:26,940 --> 01:20:29,022
Get away from me, man!

810
01:20:29,140 --> 01:20:33,145
- Lieutenant. - What happened to Gorman?

811
01:20:33,220 --> 01:20:36,463
I don't know. Maybe a concussion.

812
01:20:36,540 --> 01:20:38,861
- But he's alive. - No, he's dead!

813
01:20:38,940 --> 01:20:41,022
Wake up, pendejo, and then I'm gonna kill you!

814
01:20:41,100 --> 01:20:44,309
Back off. Right now.

815
01:20:45,780 --> 01:20:48,943
- Somebody get me a first aid kit. - Fuck!

816
01:20:49,020 --> 01:20:52,149
Hey. Hey, look.

817
01:20:52,220 --> 01:20:55,542
The sarge and Dietrich aren't dead, man.

818
01:20:55,620 --> 01:20:57,622
Their signs are real low, but they ain't dead.

819
01:20:57,700 --> 01:20:59,941
- Then we go back in there and get them. - Fuck that!

820
01:21:00,060 --> 01:21:02,516
- We don't leave our people behind... - I ain't going back in there.

821
01:21:02,540 --> 01:21:04,986
You can't help them!

822
01:21:05,060 --> 01:21:09,748
You can't. Right now they're being cocooned just like the others.

823
01:21:14,060 --> 01:21:18,304
- Oh, dear Lord Jesus, this ain't happenin', man. - Damn it.

824
01:21:18,380 --> 01:21:21,463
This can't be happenin', man. This isn't happenin'!

825
01:21:21,540 --> 01:21:25,101
All right. We got seven canisters of CN-20.

826
01:21:25,180 --> 01:21:28,502
I say we roll them in there and nerve gas the whole fucking nest.

827
01:21:28,620 --> 01:21:31,385
That's worth a try, but we don't even know if it's gonna affect them.

828
01:21:31,460 --> 01:21:35,943
Let's just bug out and call it even. Okay? What are we talking about this for?

829
01:21:36,020 --> 01:21:39,741
I say we take off and nuke the entire site from orbit.

830
01:21:42,620 --> 01:21:44,543
It's the only way to be sure.

831
01:21:44,620 --> 01:21:47,863
- Fuckin' "A"! - Hold on. Hold on one second.

832
01:21:47,940 --> 01:21:52,150
This installation has a substantial dollar value attached to it.

833
01:21:52,220 --> 01:21:54,700
They can bill me.

834
01:21:54,780 --> 01:21:59,866
Okay, look. This is an emotional moment for all of us, okay?

835
01:21:59,940 --> 01:22:03,342
I know that. But let's not make snap judgments, please.

836
01:22:03,420 --> 01:22:06,390
This is clearly... clearly an important species we're dealing with,

837
01:22:06,460 --> 01:22:09,225
and I don't think that you or I or anybody has the right...

838
01:22:09,300 --> 01:22:12,383
- to arbitrarily exterminate them. - Wrong.

839
01:22:12,460 --> 01:22:14,030
Yeah. Watch us.

840
01:22:14,100 --> 01:22:16,387
Maybe you haven't been keeping up on current events,

841
01:22:16,500 --> 01:22:19,151
but we just got our asses kicked, pal!

842
01:22:19,220 --> 01:22:22,588
Look. I'm not blind to what's going on,

843
01:22:22,660 --> 01:22:25,266
but I cannot authorize that kind of action.

844
01:22:25,340 --> 01:22:27,422
I'm sorry.

845
01:22:28,540 --> 01:22:31,464
Well, I believe Corporal Hicks...

846
01:22:31,540 --> 01:22:33,508
has authority here.

847
01:22:35,020 --> 01:22:36,909
Corporal Hicks is...

848
01:22:37,020 --> 01:22:39,387
This operation is under military jurisdiction,

849
01:22:39,460 --> 01:22:41,383
and Hicks is next in chain of command.

850
01:22:41,460 --> 01:22:43,622
Am I right, Corporal?

851
01:22:43,700 --> 01:22:45,668
Yeah.

852
01:22:46,860 --> 01:22:49,340
Yeah, that's right.

853
01:22:49,460 --> 01:22:51,635
- Yeah. Look, Ripley. - Yes.

854
01:22:51,640 --> 01:22:54,066
This is a multimillion-dollar installation, okay?

855
01:22:54,140 --> 01:22:56,063
He can't make that kind of decision.

856
01:22:56,140 --> 01:22:58,746
He's just a grunt. Uh, no offense.

857
01:22:58,820 --> 01:23:02,586
- None taken. Ferro, do you copy? - Standing by.

858
01:23:02,660 --> 01:23:05,345
Prep for dust off. We're gonna need immediate evac.

859
01:23:05,420 --> 01:23:07,343
Roger. On our way.

860
01:23:07,420 --> 01:23:12,028
I say we take off, nuke the site from orbit. It's the only way to be sure.

861
01:23:14,660 --> 01:23:16,424
Let's do it.

862
01:23:23,500 --> 01:23:27,061
Let's go. Pick it up, Hudson. Pick it up, baby.

863
01:23:32,260 --> 01:23:34,422
All right. Set him down here.

864
01:23:41,020 --> 01:23:43,068
Move it, Spunkmeyer. We're rolling.

865
01:23:48,260 --> 01:23:50,149
Hold on a second. There's something...

866
01:23:50,260 --> 01:23:52,547
Just get up here.

867
01:23:52,620 --> 01:23:55,146
I'm in. Ramp closing.

868
01:24:14,860 --> 01:24:16,828
Spunkmeyer.

869
01:24:18,020 --> 01:24:21,706
Goddamn it.

870
01:24:21,780 --> 01:24:24,101
Well, where the fuck...

871
01:24:36,860 --> 01:24:38,783
Run!

872
01:25:19,660 --> 01:25:23,460
Well, that's great. That's just fuckin' great, man.

873
01:25:23,540 --> 01:25:26,020
Now what the fuck are we supposed to do?

874
01:25:26,100 --> 01:25:28,387
We're in some real pretty shit now, man!

875
01:25:28,460 --> 01:25:30,861
Are you finished?

876
01:25:33,660 --> 01:25:35,662
You all right?

877
01:25:40,860 --> 01:25:45,070
I guess we're not gonna be leaving now, right?

878
01:25:45,140 --> 01:25:46,744
I'm sorry, Newt.

879
01:25:46,860 --> 01:25:50,785
- You don't have to be sorry. It wasn't your fault. - That's it, man.

880
01:25:50,860 --> 01:25:53,261
Game over, man! Game over!

881
01:25:53,340 --> 01:25:55,946
What the fuck are we gonna do now? What are we gonna do?

882
01:25:56,020 --> 01:26:00,469
Maybe we could build a fire. Sing a couple of songs, huh? Why don't we try that?

883
01:26:00,540 --> 01:26:03,305
We'd better get back 'cause it'll be dark soon,

884
01:26:03,380 --> 01:26:06,748
and they mostly come at night, mostly.

885
01:26:23,580 --> 01:26:27,585
That's everything, right? All right. This is absolutely everything...

886
01:26:27,660 --> 01:26:30,664
that we could salvage out of the A.P.C. wreckage.

887
01:26:30,740 --> 01:26:34,347
We got four pulse rifles with about 50 rounds each.

888
01:26:34,420 --> 01:26:36,548
That ain't so good.

889
01:26:36,620 --> 01:26:40,341
We got, uh, 15 of these M-40 grenades.

890
01:26:40,420 --> 01:26:42,343
Don't touch that.

891
01:26:42,460 --> 01:26:44,906
- Dangerous, honey. - Is that the only flamethrower?

892
01:26:45,020 --> 01:26:49,070
Yeah. It's only half full, but it's functional.

893
01:26:49,140 --> 01:26:52,906
Got another one, it's damaged... I don't know about that one.

894
01:26:52,980 --> 01:26:58,783
But the good news... we got four of these robot sentries,

895
01:26:58,860 --> 01:27:01,909
with display and scanners intact.

896
01:27:01,980 --> 01:27:05,143
They really kick ass. I think they'll come in handy.

897
01:27:05,220 --> 01:27:09,669
How long after we're declared overdue can we expect a rescue?

898
01:27:11,700 --> 01:27:13,828
Seventeen days.

899
01:27:14,820 --> 01:27:17,391
Seventeen days?

900
01:27:17,460 --> 01:27:21,351
Hey, man, I don't wanna rain on your parade, but we're not gonna last 17 hours.

901
01:27:21,420 --> 01:27:25,156
Those things are gonna come in here just like they did before. And they're gonna come in here...

902
01:27:25,180 --> 01:27:28,263
- Hudson! Hudson! - They're gonna come in here and they're gonna get us!

903
01:27:28,340 --> 01:27:30,388
This little girl survived longer than that...

904
01:27:30,460 --> 01:27:33,509
with no weapons and no training.

905
01:27:33,580 --> 01:27:35,503
Right?

906
01:27:37,900 --> 01:27:40,585
Why don't you put her in charge?

907
01:27:40,700 --> 01:27:43,510
You'd better just start dealing with it, Hudson. Listen to me.

908
01:27:43,620 --> 01:27:45,782
Hudson, just deal with it because we need you.

909
01:27:45,860 --> 01:27:47,783
And I'm sick of your bullshit.

910
01:27:47,860 --> 01:27:51,467
Now, I want you to get on a terminal and call up some kind of floor plan file.

911
01:27:51,540 --> 01:27:54,225
Do you understand? Construction blueprints. I don't care.

912
01:27:54,340 --> 01:27:56,756
Anything that shows the layout of this place. Are you listening?

913
01:27:56,780 --> 01:27:59,863
- Yeah. - I need to see air ducts.

914
01:27:59,940 --> 01:28:03,342
I need to see electrical access tunnels, subbasements,

915
01:28:03,420 --> 01:28:07,141
every possible way into this complex.

916
01:28:07,220 --> 01:28:11,669
- We don't have much time. - Okay.

917
01:28:11,780 --> 01:28:14,101
- Okay, I'm on it. - Hudson!

918
01:28:14,180 --> 01:28:18,868
Just relax.

919
01:28:22,260 --> 01:28:27,300
I'll be in med lab. I'll check on Gorman, continue my analysis.

920
01:28:27,380 --> 01:28:30,304
Fine. You do that.

921
01:28:36,540 --> 01:28:40,386
So this service tunnel must be how they're moving back and forth.

922
01:28:40,460 --> 01:28:42,940
That's right. It moves from the processing station...

923
01:28:43,020 --> 01:28:45,387
right into the sublevel here.

924
01:28:47,420 --> 01:28:50,742
Come down on that. Okay, come over.

925
01:28:50,820 --> 01:28:54,063
Hold. Go back. Okay, punch that in right there.

926
01:28:59,700 --> 01:29:01,782
No. It's back here. Okay.

927
01:29:03,300 --> 01:29:05,951
Well, there's a pressure door at this end.

928
01:29:06,060 --> 01:29:10,702
Couldn't we put one of the remote sentry units in the tunnel, and then seal that door?

929
01:29:10,780 --> 01:29:13,784
Yeah, that'll work, but we gotta figure on them getting into the complex.

930
01:29:13,860 --> 01:29:18,866
That's right, so... we repair the barricades at these two intersections.

931
01:29:18,980 --> 01:29:21,665
- Right. - And weld plate steel over these ducts...

932
01:29:21,740 --> 01:29:26,143
here and here and here.

933
01:29:26,220 --> 01:29:29,224
That way they can only come at us from these two corridors.

934
01:29:29,300 --> 01:29:34,989
All right. Then we put the other sentry units here, and here, right?

935
01:29:35,100 --> 01:29:37,546
- Right. - Outstanding.

936
01:29:37,620 --> 01:29:39,588
Now all we need is a deck of cards.

937
01:29:41,900 --> 01:29:43,982
All right, people. Let's move like we got a purpose.

938
01:29:44,100 --> 01:29:46,865
- Affirmative. - Affirmative.

939
01:30:02,100 --> 01:30:05,786
Do your thing, baby. Come on, Come on, Vasquez. Let's get the hell outta here.

940
01:30:05,860 --> 01:30:08,750
Hudson here. "A" and "B" sentries are in place and keyed.

941
01:30:08,820 --> 01:30:13,667
Roger. Stand by. Arming now. Test it, Hudson.

942
01:30:13,780 --> 01:30:16,181
- Do it! - Fire in the hole!

943
01:30:19,420 --> 01:30:22,230
Okay, great. Let's get the hell outta here!

944
01:30:22,300 --> 01:30:25,782
We're sealing the tunnel. Come on, baby.

945
01:30:37,940 --> 01:30:39,863
For what it's worth.

946
01:30:41,820 --> 01:30:44,107
Here. I want you to put this on.

947
01:30:45,500 --> 01:30:47,741
- What's it for? - It's a locator.

948
01:30:47,820 --> 01:30:51,302
Then I can find you anywhere in the complex on this.

949
01:30:53,140 --> 01:30:57,225
- It's just a precaution. - Thanks.

950
01:30:57,300 --> 01:31:00,110
Doesn't mean we're engaged or anything.

951
01:31:00,180 --> 01:31:02,182
All right, what's next?

952
01:31:31,780 --> 01:31:33,828
Last stop.

953
01:31:37,820 --> 01:31:39,743
Get in.

954
01:31:39,820 --> 01:31:43,950
Scoot down. That's good.

955
01:31:44,020 --> 01:31:48,070
Now, you lie here and have a nap. You're very tired.

956
01:31:48,140 --> 01:31:51,508
I don't want to. I have scary dreams.

957
01:31:53,900 --> 01:31:56,983
Well, I bet Casey doesn't have scary dreams.

958
01:31:57,060 --> 01:31:58,983
Let's take a look.

959
01:31:59,060 --> 01:32:01,427
Nope. Nothing bad in there.

960
01:32:01,500 --> 01:32:05,789
See? Maybe you could just try to be like her, hmm?

961
01:32:05,860 --> 01:32:08,386
Ripley, she doesn't have bad dreams...

962
01:32:08,460 --> 01:32:11,509
because she's just a piece of plastic.

963
01:32:11,580 --> 01:32:15,107
Right. I'm sorry, Newt.

964
01:32:21,780 --> 01:32:24,067
There.

965
01:32:24,140 --> 01:32:27,030
My mommy always said there were no monsters...

966
01:32:27,100 --> 01:32:30,422
no real ones... but there are.

967
01:32:31,780 --> 01:32:33,748
Yes, there are, aren't there?

968
01:32:35,820 --> 01:32:38,141
Why do they tell little kids that?

969
01:32:40,020 --> 01:32:41,943
Most of the time it's true.

970
01:32:42,020 --> 01:32:45,502
Did one of those things grow inside her?

971
01:32:45,580 --> 01:32:48,390
I don't know, Newt.

972
01:32:48,460 --> 01:32:50,428
That's the truth.

973
01:32:50,500 --> 01:32:55,062
Isn't that how babies come? I mean, people babies?

974
01:32:55,220 --> 01:32:58,747
- They grow inside you. - Oh, that's very different.

975
01:32:58,820 --> 01:33:00,743
Did you ever have a baby?

976
01:33:00,820 --> 01:33:04,142
Yes, I did. I had a little girl.

977
01:33:04,260 --> 01:33:08,822
- Where is she? - She's gone.

978
01:33:10,620 --> 01:33:12,588
You mean dead.

979
01:33:14,180 --> 01:33:15,180
Here.

980
01:33:16,500 --> 01:33:18,343
Take this.

981
01:33:19,860 --> 01:33:21,828
For luck.

982
01:33:25,020 --> 01:33:26,988
There's that.

983
01:33:29,140 --> 01:33:31,063
Don't go, please.

984
01:33:31,140 --> 01:33:34,701
Newt, I'm gonna be right in the next room.

985
01:33:34,780 --> 01:33:36,703
And you see that camera right up there?

986
01:33:36,780 --> 01:33:39,590
I can see you right through that camera,

987
01:33:39,660 --> 01:33:42,027
all the time to see if you're safe.

988
01:33:46,380 --> 01:33:49,065
I'm not gonna leave you, Newt.

989
01:33:49,140 --> 01:33:53,065
I mean that. That's a promise.

990
01:33:53,140 --> 01:33:55,825
You promise?

991
01:33:55,900 --> 01:33:58,187
I cross my heart.

992
01:33:58,260 --> 01:34:02,584
- And hope to die? - And hope to die.

993
01:34:17,460 --> 01:34:21,909
Now go to sleep, and don't dream.

994
01:34:26,100 --> 01:34:28,068
Sneak.

995
01:34:36,820 --> 01:34:41,064
The molecular acid oxidizes after the creature's death, completely neutralizing it.

996
01:34:41,140 --> 01:34:44,636
Bishop, you know, that's very interesting, but it doesn't really get us anywhere, does it?

997
01:34:44,660 --> 01:34:47,186
I'm trying to figure out what we're dealing with here.

998
01:34:47,260 --> 01:34:49,342
Let's go through it again.

999
01:34:49,460 --> 01:34:51,667
They grab the colonists, they move them over there...

1000
01:34:51,740 --> 01:34:56,064
and they immobilize them to be hosts for more of these.

1001
01:34:56,140 --> 01:34:59,986
Which would mean that there would have to be a lot of these parasites, right?

1002
01:35:00,060 --> 01:35:02,267
One for each colonist. That's over 100, at least.

1003
01:35:02,340 --> 01:35:04,263
Yes. That follows.

1004
01:35:04,340 --> 01:35:08,390
But each one of these things comes from an egg, right?

1005
01:35:10,940 --> 01:35:12,863
So who's laying these eggs?

1006
01:35:12,940 --> 01:35:16,023
I'm not sure.

1007
01:35:16,100 --> 01:35:18,068
It must be something we haven't seen yet.

1008
01:35:18,140 --> 01:35:20,347
Hey, maybe it's like an ant hive.

1009
01:35:20,420 --> 01:35:22,468
Bees, man. Bees have hives.

1010
01:35:22,540 --> 01:35:27,706
You know what I mean. There's, like, one female that runs the whole show.

1011
01:35:27,820 --> 01:35:30,187
- Yes, the queen. - Yeah, the mama.

1012
01:35:30,260 --> 01:35:32,627
She's badass, man. I mean, big.

1013
01:35:32,740 --> 01:35:35,311
- These things ain't ants, estúpido. - I know that.

1014
01:35:35,380 --> 01:35:40,022
Bishop, I want these specimens destroyed as soon as you're finished with them.

1015
01:35:40,100 --> 01:35:43,024
- Is that clear? - Mr. Burke gave instructions...

1016
01:35:43,140 --> 01:35:46,940
that they were to be kept alive in stasis for return to the company labs.

1017
01:35:49,180 --> 01:35:51,148
He was very specific about it.

1018
01:35:52,540 --> 01:35:56,545
Look, those two specimens are worth millions to the bio-weapons division, right?

1019
01:35:56,620 --> 01:36:00,022
Now, if you're smart, we can both come out of this heroes,

1020
01:36:00,100 --> 01:36:03,309
and we will be set up for life.

1021
01:36:04,340 --> 01:36:06,946
You're crazy, Burke. Do you know that?

1022
01:36:07,020 --> 01:36:11,184
Do you really think you can get a dangerous organism like that past I.C.C. quarantine?

1023
01:36:11,260 --> 01:36:14,150
How can they impound it if they don't know about it?

1024
01:36:14,220 --> 01:36:17,303
But they will know about it, Burke, from me.

1025
01:36:17,380 --> 01:36:21,590
Just like they'll know that you were responsible for the deaths of 157 colonists.

1026
01:36:21,700 --> 01:36:24,146
- Wait a second. - You sent them to that ship.

1027
01:36:24,260 --> 01:36:26,342
- You're wrong. - I just checked the colony log.

1028
01:36:26,420 --> 01:36:30,311
Directive dated 6-12-79, signed Burke, Carter J.

1029
01:36:30,380 --> 01:36:33,304
You sent them out there, and you didn't even warn them.

1030
01:36:33,420 --> 01:36:35,866
- Why didn't you warn them, Burke? - Okay, look.

1031
01:36:35,940 --> 01:36:38,476
What if that ship didn't even exist? Do you ever think about that?

1032
01:36:38,500 --> 01:36:42,186
I didn't know. So now if I went and made a major security situation out of it,

1033
01:36:42,300 --> 01:36:45,756
everybody steps in, administration steps in, and there's no exclusive rights for anybody.

1034
01:36:45,780 --> 01:36:49,830
Nobody wins. So I made a decision, and it was wrong.

1035
01:36:49,900 --> 01:36:52,631
It was a bad call, Ripley. It was a bad call.

1036
01:36:52,740 --> 01:36:54,424
- Bad call? - Right.

1037
01:36:54,500 --> 01:36:56,104
These people are dead, Burke!

1038
01:36:56,180 --> 01:36:58,626
Don't you have any idea what you've done here?

1039
01:36:58,700 --> 01:37:01,624
I'm gonna make sure that they nail you right to the wall for this!

1040
01:37:01,700 --> 01:37:03,941
You're not gonna sleaze your way out of this one.

1041
01:37:04,020 --> 01:37:06,227
Right to the wall.

1042
01:37:08,060 --> 01:37:11,109
Ripley. I...

1043
01:37:11,180 --> 01:37:13,182
You know, I expected more from you.

1044
01:37:13,260 --> 01:37:16,230
I thought... you'd be smarter than this.

1045
01:37:16,300 --> 01:37:19,668
Well, I'm happy to disappoint you.

1046
01:37:33,260 --> 01:37:35,661
- What is it? What's going on? - They're coming.

1047
01:37:35,780 --> 01:37:38,226
- Where? - In the tunnel.

1048
01:37:39,780 --> 01:37:45,264
Here we go. "A" and "B" gun tracking far end. Multiple targets.

1049
01:37:51,060 --> 01:37:52,903
Those ammo counters go.

1050
01:37:55,580 --> 01:37:57,708
"B" gun's down 50%.

1051
01:37:58,900 --> 01:38:01,141
Man, it's a shooting gallery down there.

1052
01:38:05,100 --> 01:38:06,864
Sixty rounds left on "B."

1053
01:38:06,940 --> 01:38:10,103
Forty. Twenty. Ten.

1054
01:38:10,180 --> 01:38:12,421
"B" gun's dry. Twenty on "A."

1055
01:38:13,700 --> 01:38:16,909
Ten. Five.

1056
01:38:19,780 --> 01:38:21,464
That's it.

1057
01:38:21,540 --> 01:38:24,783
Jesus, they were wall-to-wall in there.

1058
01:38:28,740 --> 01:38:30,742
They're at the pressure door.

1059
01:38:32,340 --> 01:38:34,308
Man, listen to that.

1060
01:38:34,380 --> 01:38:38,066
Bishop here. I'm afraid I have some bad news.

1061
01:38:38,140 --> 01:38:39,140
Well, that's a switch.

1062
01:38:42,220 --> 01:38:45,030
It's very pretty, Bishop, but what are we looking for?

1063
01:38:45,100 --> 01:38:48,661
That's it. Emergency venting.

1064
01:38:48,740 --> 01:38:53,348
Oh, that's beautiful, man. Oh, man, that... that just beats it all.

1065
01:38:53,460 --> 01:38:56,304
- How long till it blows? - Four hours.

1066
01:38:56,420 --> 01:38:59,503
With a blast radius of 30 kilometers,

1067
01:38:59,580 --> 01:39:03,187
equal to about 40 megatons.

1068
01:39:03,340 --> 01:39:06,787
We got problems. HUDSON: I don't believe this. I don't fucking believe this.

1069
01:39:06,860 --> 01:39:09,386
Vasquez, close the shutters.

1070
01:39:09,460 --> 01:39:11,622
Why can't we shut it down from here?

1071
01:39:11,700 --> 01:39:13,623
I'm sorry. The crash caused too much damage.

1072
01:39:13,700 --> 01:39:16,271
An overload... is inevitable at this point.

1073
01:39:16,340 --> 01:39:19,264
Oh, man, and I was getting short.

1074
01:39:19,340 --> 01:39:22,662
Four more weeks and out. Now I'm gonna buy it on this rock.

1075
01:39:22,780 --> 01:39:24,862
- It ain't half fair, man. - Hudson, give us a break!

1076
01:39:24,940 --> 01:39:27,511
Four more weeks. Oh, man.

1077
01:39:27,580 --> 01:39:30,823
We've got to get the other drop ship from the Sulaco.

1078
01:39:30,900 --> 01:39:33,870
I mean, there must be some way of bringing it down on remote.

1079
01:39:33,940 --> 01:39:37,422
How? The transmitter was on the A.P.C. It's wasted.

1080
01:39:37,580 --> 01:39:40,789
I don't care how, but we'd better think of something. We'd better think of a way.

1081
01:39:40,900 --> 01:39:43,744
- Think of what? We're fucked! We're doomed! - Shut up!

1082
01:39:43,820 --> 01:39:46,630
Shut up! What about the colony transmitters?

1083
01:39:46,700 --> 01:39:49,510
The uplink tower down at the other end. Why can't we use that?

1084
01:39:49,580 --> 01:39:52,550
No, I checked. The hardware in between here and there was damaged.

1085
01:39:52,620 --> 01:39:54,543
We can't align the dish.

1086
01:39:54,620 --> 01:39:57,066
Well, somebody's gonna have to go out there,

1087
01:39:57,140 --> 01:40:00,064
take a portable terminal, go out there and patch in manually.

1088
01:40:00,140 --> 01:40:05,180
Oh, yeah, sure. With those things running around? You can count me out.

1089
01:40:05,300 --> 01:40:07,379
- Yeah I guess we can just count you out of everything. - I'll go. I'll go.

1090
01:40:07,380 --> 01:40:09,276
That's right, man. Why don't you go, man?

1091
01:40:09,300 --> 01:40:11,143
- I'll go. - What?

1092
01:40:11,220 --> 01:40:15,589
I'll go. I mean, I'm the only one qualified to remote pilot the ship anyway.

1093
01:40:15,660 --> 01:40:20,029
Yeah, right, man. Bishop should go. Good idea.

1094
01:40:20,100 --> 01:40:22,262
Believe me, I'd prefer not to.

1095
01:40:22,340 --> 01:40:25,264
I may be synthetic, but I'm not stupid.

1096
01:40:37,060 --> 01:40:38,949
How long?

1097
01:40:39,060 --> 01:40:42,303
This conduit runs almost to the uplink assembly... 180 meters.

1098
01:40:42,420 --> 01:40:45,708
- Say 40 minutes to crawl down there... - Right.

1099
01:40:45,780 --> 01:40:49,546
An hour to, patch in and align the antenna.

1100
01:40:50,620 --> 01:40:52,907
Thirty minutes to prep the ship,

1101
01:40:53,020 --> 01:40:56,229
- and about 50 minutes flight time. - It's gonna be close.

1102
01:41:00,740 --> 01:41:03,471
- Good luck. - See you soon.

1103
01:41:04,900 --> 01:41:08,700
Watch your fingers.

1104
01:41:11,700 --> 01:41:13,065
Vaya con Dios, man.

1105
01:41:24,860 --> 01:41:29,468
This is unbelievable. Twenty meters and closing.

1106
01:41:29,580 --> 01:41:31,662
- Fifteen. - How many?

1107
01:41:31,780 --> 01:41:34,351
Can't tell. Lots.

1108
01:41:35,940 --> 01:41:39,183
"D" gun's down 50%.

1109
01:41:41,220 --> 01:41:44,349
"C" gun's right behind it.

1110
01:41:46,300 --> 01:41:49,509
Stopping them. It ain't stopping them.

1111
01:41:49,580 --> 01:41:54,586
- 150 rounds on "D." - Come on. Come on, baby.

1112
01:41:54,660 --> 01:41:56,947
Hundred rounds.

1113
01:41:57,020 --> 01:41:59,705
Come on! Come on!

1114
01:42:04,700 --> 01:42:06,225
"D" gun's down to 20.

1115
01:42:07,460 --> 01:42:09,906
10.

1116
01:42:11,140 --> 01:42:12,551
Damn it!

1117
01:42:14,180 --> 01:42:17,184
Wait! They're retreating.

1118
01:42:22,420 --> 01:42:25,151
The guns stopped them.

1119
01:42:27,020 --> 01:42:28,988
You're right.

1120
01:42:36,380 --> 01:42:38,303
Next time they walk right up and knock.

1121
01:42:38,380 --> 01:42:40,348
Yeah, but they don't know that.

1122
01:42:40,420 --> 01:42:43,185
They're probably looking for other ways to get in.

1123
01:42:44,220 --> 01:42:46,109
That'll take 'em a while.

1124
01:42:46,220 --> 01:42:48,700
- Maybe we got 'em demoralized. - Shut up!

1125
01:42:50,060 --> 01:42:52,506
I want you two walking perimeter.

1126
01:42:54,100 --> 01:42:56,671
Move!

1127
01:43:02,900 --> 01:43:05,107
Hey, listen.

1128
01:43:05,180 --> 01:43:08,104
We're all in strung-out shape,

1129
01:43:08,180 --> 01:43:11,502
but stay frosty and alert.

1130
01:43:12,900 --> 01:43:15,790
We can't afford to let one of those bastards in here.

1131
01:43:15,860 --> 01:43:18,022
All right. Vámonos.

1132
01:43:28,940 --> 01:43:30,942
How long's it been since you got any sleep?

1133
01:43:31,020 --> 01:43:34,627
Twenty-four hours?

1134
01:43:34,700 --> 01:43:38,022
Hicks, I'm not gonna end up like those others.

1135
01:43:38,100 --> 01:43:40,944
You'll take care of it, won't you?

1136
01:43:42,500 --> 01:43:47,062
If it comes to that, I'll do us both.

1137
01:43:48,780 --> 01:43:51,511
Listen, let's just make sure it doesn't come to that.

1138
01:43:51,620 --> 01:43:55,181
- All right? - All right.

1139
01:43:55,300 --> 01:44:00,511
Hey, I want to introduce you to a personal friend of mine.

1140
01:44:00,580 --> 01:44:04,505
This is an M-41 A pulse rifle, 10 millimeter,

1141
01:44:04,580 --> 01:44:08,426
with an over-and-under 30 millimeter pump-action grenade launcher.

1142
01:44:08,500 --> 01:44:10,468
Feel the weight.

1143
01:44:17,380 --> 01:44:19,667
Okay, what do I do?

1144
01:44:25,100 --> 01:44:27,751
- Okay, pull it in tight here. - Right.

1145
01:44:27,860 --> 01:44:30,147
- Uh-huh. Lean into it. - Mm-hmm.

1146
01:44:30,220 --> 01:44:32,905
All right. Now, it will kick some.

1147
01:44:32,980 --> 01:44:36,541
All right. When the counter reads zero here, you...

1148
01:44:36,660 --> 01:44:38,901
- I press this up? - That's right.

1149
01:44:40,980 --> 01:44:44,143
Get another one in quick. Slap it in hard.

1150
01:44:44,260 --> 01:44:47,264
- Right. - And you're ready to rock and roll.

1151
01:44:47,380 --> 01:44:50,190
- What's this? - That's the grenade launcher...

1152
01:44:50,260 --> 01:44:53,025
I don't think you want to mess with that.

1153
01:44:53,100 --> 01:44:57,105
You started this. Show me everything.

1154
01:44:57,180 --> 01:44:59,148
I can handle myself.

1155
01:45:00,740 --> 01:45:02,708
Yeah, I noticed.

1156
01:45:12,820 --> 01:45:14,788
How do you feel?

1157
01:45:14,860 --> 01:45:18,387
All right, I guess. One hell of a hangover.

1158
01:45:19,900 --> 01:45:22,107
- Look, Ripley, I just want... - Forget it.

1159
01:45:22,220 --> 01:45:24,188
Excuse me.

1160
01:46:19,180 --> 01:46:23,947
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh. It's okay. It's okay.

1161
01:47:34,660 --> 01:47:38,107
Newt, Newt, wake up.

1162
01:47:38,180 --> 01:47:40,103
- Wha... - Be quiet.

1163
01:47:40,180 --> 01:47:42,182
We're in trouble.

1164
01:47:59,700 --> 01:48:01,509
No!

1165
01:48:01,580 --> 01:48:04,231
Move, Newt!

1166
01:48:24,700 --> 01:48:26,623
Hey!

1167
01:48:35,660 --> 01:48:39,984
Help! Help!

1168
01:48:40,060 --> 01:48:42,028
- Somebody! - Hicks!

1169
01:48:42,100 --> 01:48:44,023
Say again, Bishop.

1170
01:48:44,100 --> 01:48:47,468
You've got it into auto-refuel mode, and it's sequencing right?

1171
01:48:47,580 --> 01:48:50,584
- That's right. - Okay, good. Stay on it.

1172
01:48:50,700 --> 01:48:54,261
Get back to me when you've activated the launch cycle.

1173
01:48:54,340 --> 01:48:57,583
- Roger. - He's at the uplink tower.

1174
01:48:57,700 --> 01:49:00,226
- Good. - Terrific.

1175
01:49:01,900 --> 01:49:04,949
- Hicks! Hicks! Hicks! - Help!

1176
01:49:05,020 --> 01:49:07,591
- Help! Help! - Hicks, help us!

1177
01:49:07,660 --> 01:49:11,790
- Break the glass! Break it. Break it. - Yes.

1178
01:49:11,860 --> 01:49:13,862
I'll try.

1179
01:49:34,100 --> 01:49:36,580
Ripley, I'm scared.

1180
01:49:36,660 --> 01:49:38,662
Me too.

1181
01:49:44,140 --> 01:49:46,142
Stay here.

1182
01:49:57,940 --> 01:50:00,989
- It's the med lab. - Hudson!

1183
01:50:01,060 --> 01:50:04,382
Vasquez, meet me in med lab. We got a fire.

1184
01:50:04,500 --> 01:50:06,502
We're on our way.

1185
01:50:09,380 --> 01:50:11,382
They're coming, Newt.

1186
01:50:43,940 --> 01:50:46,022
Shoot it out!

1187
01:50:50,020 --> 01:50:51,909
- Hudson! - Jesus.

1188
01:50:55,500 --> 01:50:57,821
Christ, kid, look out!

1189
01:51:05,740 --> 01:51:06,741
Fucking die.

1190
01:51:18,620 --> 01:51:21,863
- Over there! Ready? - Yeah! Yeah!

1191
01:51:21,940 --> 01:51:23,590
Now!

1192
01:51:27,060 --> 01:51:28,949
- Hudson? - Yeah. All clear.

1193
01:51:29,060 --> 01:51:31,631
Nailed the other one. It's history, man.

1194
01:51:33,020 --> 01:51:34,943
Jesus.

1195
01:51:36,100 --> 01:51:39,707
- Burke... - It was Burke.

1196
01:51:41,940 --> 01:51:45,183
I say we grease this rat-fuck son of a bitch right now.

1197
01:51:45,260 --> 01:51:48,184
Just doesn't make any goddamn sense.

1198
01:51:51,140 --> 01:51:55,190
He figured that he could get an alien back through quarantine...

1199
01:51:55,260 --> 01:51:57,991
if one of us was impregnated...

1200
01:51:59,260 --> 01:52:01,467
whatever you call it...

1201
01:52:01,540 --> 01:52:04,146
and then frozen for the trip home.

1202
01:52:04,220 --> 01:52:08,270
Nobody would know about the embryos we were carrying...

1203
01:52:08,340 --> 01:52:10,388
me and Newt.

1204
01:52:12,220 --> 01:52:14,188
Wait a minute, now. We'd all know.

1205
01:52:14,260 --> 01:52:16,547
Yes. The only way he could do it...

1206
01:52:16,620 --> 01:52:20,386
is if he sabotaged certain freezers on the way home.

1207
01:52:20,460 --> 01:52:23,031
Namely yours.

1208
01:52:23,140 --> 01:52:26,986
Then he could jettison the bodies and make up any story he liked.

1209
01:52:27,100 --> 01:52:32,470
Fuck! He's dead. You're dog meat, pal.

1210
01:52:33,460 --> 01:52:35,383
This is so nuts.

1211
01:52:35,460 --> 01:52:38,111
I mean, listen... Listen to what you're saying.

1212
01:52:38,180 --> 01:52:40,865
It's paranoid delusion.

1213
01:52:40,940 --> 01:52:45,264
It's really sad. It's pathetic.

1214
01:52:45,340 --> 01:52:49,140
You know, Burke, I don't know which species is worse.

1215
01:52:49,220 --> 01:52:52,542
You don't see them fucking each other over for a goddamn percentage.

1216
01:52:52,620 --> 01:52:55,749
All right. We waste him. No offense.

1217
01:52:55,820 --> 01:52:57,504
No! He's gotta go back...

1218
01:52:59,660 --> 01:53:02,311
- They cut the power. - What do you mean, they cut the power?

1219
01:53:02,380 --> 01:53:03,996
How could they cut the power, man? They're animals.

1220
01:53:04,020 --> 01:53:06,626
I want you two with trackers, checking the corridors! Move!

1221
01:53:06,700 --> 01:53:08,623
- Gorman, watch Burke! - I got him.

1222
01:53:08,700 --> 01:53:11,021
Newt, stay close.

1223
01:53:14,500 --> 01:53:17,583
- I'll go this side. - You do that, man.

1224
01:53:41,340 --> 01:53:44,105
- Anything? - There's something.

1225
01:53:44,220 --> 01:53:47,429
It's inside the complex.

1226
01:53:47,500 --> 01:53:49,502
You're just reading me.

1227
01:53:50,460 --> 01:53:52,383
No, no, it ain't you.

1228
01:53:54,540 --> 01:53:58,226
They're inside... inside the perimeter. They're in here.

1229
01:53:58,300 --> 01:54:01,782
Hudson, stay cool! Vasquez?

1230
01:54:08,500 --> 01:54:10,104
Hudson may be right.

1231
01:54:10,220 --> 01:54:13,349
- Get back, both of you! - The signal's weird.

1232
01:54:14,740 --> 01:54:17,425
Must be some interference or something.

1233
01:54:17,500 --> 01:54:19,423
There's movement all over the place!

1234
01:54:19,500 --> 01:54:22,822
Get back to Operations. It's game time.

1235
01:54:22,900 --> 01:54:25,301
Newt.

1236
01:54:26,820 --> 01:54:29,710
Seal the door. Hurry!

1237
01:54:29,780 --> 01:54:33,262
Come on! Come on! Come on! Get back!

1238
01:54:33,340 --> 01:54:35,263
Work fast.

1239
01:54:38,620 --> 01:54:41,829
Cover your eyes, Newt. Don't look at the light.

1240
01:54:41,900 --> 01:54:44,904
Movement. Signal's clean.

1241
01:54:44,980 --> 01:54:46,903
Range, Twenty meters.

1242
01:54:46,980 --> 01:54:49,142
They found a way in, something we missed.

1243
01:54:49,220 --> 01:54:51,143
We didn't miss anything.

1244
01:54:51,220 --> 01:54:55,020
Eighteen, Seventeen meters.

1245
01:54:55,100 --> 01:54:57,501
Something under the floor, not in the plans. I don't know.

1246
01:54:57,580 --> 01:54:59,662
- Fifteen meters. - Ripley!

1247
01:54:59,740 --> 01:55:03,222
- Definitely inside the barricades. - Let's go.

1248
01:55:04,860 --> 01:55:06,836
- Thirteen meters. - That's right outside the door.

1249
01:55:06,860 --> 01:55:09,511
- Hicks, Vasquez, get back! - Man, this is a big fucking signal.

1250
01:55:09,580 --> 01:55:12,789
- How you doing, Vasquez? Talk to me. - Almost there.

1251
01:55:14,420 --> 01:55:16,787
That's it.

1252
01:55:16,860 --> 01:55:21,184
Twelve meters. Eleven.

1253
01:55:21,260 --> 01:55:23,740
- Ten. - Then they're right on us.

1254
01:55:23,860 --> 01:55:27,103
- Nine meters. - Remember... short, controlled bursts.

1255
01:55:27,180 --> 01:55:28,511
Eight meters.

1256
01:55:31,500 --> 01:55:34,185
Seven.

1257
01:55:34,260 --> 01:55:37,184
- Six. - It can't be. That's inside the room.

1258
01:55:37,260 --> 01:55:40,309
- It's reading right, man. Look! - Well, you're not reading it right.

1259
01:55:42,900 --> 01:55:47,508
Five meters, man. Four. What the hell?

1260
01:55:50,180 --> 01:55:53,741
- Oh, my God. Oh, sh... - Give me the light.

1261
01:56:12,340 --> 01:56:14,786
There they go! Over there! Get them!

1262
01:56:14,860 --> 01:56:19,582
Come on! Come on! Get 'em!

1263
01:56:19,660 --> 01:56:22,982
Do something, Gorman!

1264
01:56:23,060 --> 01:56:26,781
- Get them! Look out! - There's more of them! There's more of them!

1265
01:56:26,860 --> 01:56:30,990
Medical! Get to Medical! Do it! Now!

1266
01:56:31,060 --> 01:56:35,190
Hudson, look out! Look out!

1267
01:56:35,260 --> 01:56:39,549
Now!

1268
01:56:41,620 --> 01:56:43,782
Burke!

1269
01:56:43,900 --> 01:56:46,744
Open this door!

1270
01:56:46,860 --> 01:56:49,625
Burke! Open it!

1271
01:56:51,740 --> 01:56:53,424
Come on let's go! Fall back!

1272
01:56:56,620 --> 01:56:58,827
Go!

1273
01:56:58,900 --> 01:57:01,744
- Die, motherfucker! - Burke!

1274
01:57:01,820 --> 01:57:05,427
Hudson! Hudson!

1275
01:57:05,500 --> 01:57:10,506
Motherfucker! Come on! Come on! Come and get it, baby! Come on!

1276
01:57:10,580 --> 01:57:14,221
I don't got all day! Come on! Come on! Come on, you bastard!

1277
01:57:14,340 --> 01:57:17,105
Come on! You too! Oh, you want some of this?

1278
01:57:17,180 --> 01:57:19,467
Fuck you!

1279
01:57:20,420 --> 01:57:23,185
Fuck you! Hicks! Hicks!

1280
01:57:23,260 --> 01:57:25,911
Hudson!

1281
01:57:34,020 --> 01:57:36,466
Come on. Let's go!

1282
01:57:37,020 --> 01:57:39,307
It's locked!

1283
01:57:56,580 --> 01:58:00,301
- Got it! Let's go! Let's go! - Go! Go!

1284
01:58:02,900 --> 01:58:05,790
- Move, Gorman! - Seal it!

1285
01:58:06,820 --> 01:58:11,144
Burke! Goddamn you! Open this door!

1286
01:58:20,140 --> 01:58:23,747
Get back!

1287
01:58:23,820 --> 01:58:26,061
- Hurry up. - Gorman, get out of the way!

1288
01:58:26,180 --> 01:58:29,184
- Ripley, this way! - What...

1289
01:58:29,260 --> 01:58:31,149
Wait. Get behind me.

1290
01:58:31,220 --> 01:58:35,350
Whatever you're gonna do, do it fast!

1291
01:58:36,660 --> 01:58:39,504
- Hicks! - Go! Come on. Let's go.

1292
01:58:41,180 --> 01:58:42,670
Move!

1293
01:58:49,620 --> 01:58:53,147
- Which way is it to the landing field from here? - This way.

1294
01:58:57,740 --> 01:59:00,550
Go right.

1295
01:59:02,820 --> 01:59:04,788
This way. This way.

1296
01:59:13,420 --> 01:59:16,867
- Which way? - Straight ahead and left.

1297
01:59:16,940 --> 01:59:20,547
Bishop, do you read me? Come in. Over.

1298
01:59:20,620 --> 01:59:22,509
The ship is on its way.

1299
01:59:22,580 --> 01:59:25,663
E.T.A., 16 minutes.

1300
01:59:25,740 --> 01:59:28,550
Stand by there. We're on our way.

1301
01:59:39,820 --> 01:59:41,788
- Which way now? - That way.

1302
01:59:41,860 --> 01:59:44,909
- No, wait. This way. - You sure?

1303
01:59:46,500 --> 01:59:49,344
Vasquez, move!

1304
01:59:51,940 --> 01:59:54,102
- Right up here. It's just up here. - Hicks!

1305
01:59:54,180 --> 01:59:57,070
We're almost there.

1306
01:59:57,140 --> 02:00:00,428
Newt, wait! Newt!

1307
02:00:24,420 --> 02:00:26,388
Vasquez!

1308
02:00:26,460 --> 02:00:28,781
Go!

1309
02:00:30,940 --> 02:00:33,466
Oh, no!

1310
02:00:44,700 --> 02:00:47,067
Newt.

1311
02:00:47,140 --> 02:00:50,462
Up there. There's a shortcut across the roof.

1312
02:00:50,540 --> 02:00:52,622
Hicks.

1313
02:01:02,060 --> 02:01:04,188
You always were an asshole, Gorman.

1314
02:01:22,580 --> 02:01:24,787
- Newt! God! - Ripley!

1315
02:01:24,860 --> 02:01:27,147
Newt!

1316
02:01:27,220 --> 02:01:30,349
Hicks! Hicks, get her! Hurry!

1317
02:01:34,780 --> 02:01:37,260
- Hold on, Newt! - I'm slipping!

1318
02:01:37,340 --> 02:01:39,547
- Don't let go. - Ripley!

1319
02:01:39,620 --> 02:01:42,669
- Hold on. Gotcha! - Help!

1320
02:01:43,700 --> 02:01:46,146
I gotcha.

1321
02:01:46,220 --> 02:01:49,110
Newt!

1322
02:01:49,220 --> 02:01:51,063
No!

1323
02:01:54,460 --> 02:01:57,270
Come on. We can find her with this.

1324
02:01:57,380 --> 02:02:01,066
- Stay where you are, Newt. - Ripley!

1325
02:02:01,140 --> 02:02:04,269
We're coming.

1326
02:02:13,460 --> 02:02:15,462
Ripley!

1327
02:02:17,940 --> 02:02:21,626
This way.

1328
02:02:23,220 --> 02:02:26,542
- She's close. - Newt!

1329
02:02:29,220 --> 02:02:31,143
Ripley!

1330
02:02:31,220 --> 02:02:33,700
Where are you? Can you hear me?

1331
02:02:35,060 --> 02:02:36,983
- Newt! - Here!

1332
02:02:37,060 --> 02:02:39,267
- I'm here! - Where?

1333
02:02:43,340 --> 02:02:46,389
Newt, are you okay?

1334
02:02:46,460 --> 02:02:49,270
We'll have to cut it.

1335
02:02:49,340 --> 02:02:52,742
Climb down, honey. We've gotta cut through.

1336
02:02:59,980 --> 02:03:01,903
Newt?

1337
02:03:01,980 --> 02:03:05,268
Now, don't move. Stay very still.

1338
02:03:05,340 --> 02:03:07,342
Okay.

1339
02:03:07,420 --> 02:03:10,105
We're almost there. Hang in there, okay?

1340
02:03:17,260 --> 02:03:19,024
- Hicks. Hurry. - I know.

1341
02:03:19,140 --> 02:03:21,620
- I know! - I mean it!

1342
02:03:35,260 --> 02:03:38,184
Newt? Newt, just stay still.

1343
02:03:41,380 --> 02:03:43,587
Almost there.

1344
02:03:43,660 --> 02:03:45,344
No!

1345
02:03:46,820 --> 02:03:48,902
Newt!

1346
02:03:58,700 --> 02:04:02,182
No! No!

1347
02:04:02,300 --> 02:04:04,462
- Let's go. - No!

1348
02:04:04,540 --> 02:04:06,747
No! No! They don't kill you!

1349
02:04:06,820 --> 02:04:08,948
They... They don't kill you! They...

1350
02:04:09,020 --> 02:04:10,909
She's alive! She's alive!

1351
02:04:10,980 --> 02:04:13,426
All right. I believe you. She's alive.

1352
02:04:13,500 --> 02:04:16,185
We've got to go. Now!

1353
02:04:31,060 --> 02:04:33,028
Go!

1354
02:04:46,580 --> 02:04:51,063
- Hicks. - Get it off!

1355
02:04:51,140 --> 02:04:53,461
Get it off!

1356
02:04:59,700 --> 02:05:03,546
Here.

1357
02:05:07,820 --> 02:05:09,902
Go.

1358
02:05:12,260 --> 02:05:14,467
Come on. You can make it.

1359
02:05:37,740 --> 02:05:41,028
Bishop, how much time?

1360
02:05:41,100 --> 02:05:42,864
Plenty. Twenty-six minutes.

1361
02:05:43,020 --> 02:05:46,388
- We're not leaving. - We're not?

1362
02:07:10,700 --> 02:07:15,103
- Ripley... - I don't wanna hear about it, Bishop. She's alive. There's still time.

1363
02:07:15,180 --> 02:07:18,309
In 19 minutes, this area is gonna be a cloud of vapor the size of Nebraska.

1364
02:07:18,420 --> 02:07:21,230
- Hicks, don't let him leave. - We ain't going anywhere.

1365
02:07:23,700 --> 02:07:26,749
- See you, Hicks. - Dwayne.

1366
02:07:26,820 --> 02:07:29,630
It's Dwayne.

1367
02:07:31,380 --> 02:07:33,303
Ellen.

1368
02:07:33,380 --> 02:07:37,021
Don't be gone long, Ellen.

1369
02:07:44,140 --> 02:07:47,223
Attention. Emergency.

1370
02:07:47,300 --> 02:07:51,350
All personnel must evacuate immediately.

1371
02:07:51,420 --> 02:07:54,264
You now have 15 minutes...

1372
02:07:54,340 --> 02:07:56,627
to reach minimum safe distance.

1373
02:08:42,940 --> 02:08:46,387
Attention. Emergency.

1374
02:08:46,460 --> 02:08:50,704
All personnel must evacuate immediately.

1375
02:08:50,780 --> 02:08:53,545
You now have 14 minutes...

1376
02:08:53,620 --> 02:08:56,271
to reach minimum safe distance.

1377
02:11:46,820 --> 02:11:51,144
Oh.

1378
02:12:36,740 --> 02:12:40,426
- Ripley! Ripley! - Newt.

1379
02:12:54,340 --> 02:12:58,629
Grab on to me! Hold on!

1380
02:16:49,580 --> 02:16:51,582
Let's go!

1381
02:16:54,540 --> 02:16:57,020
Behind us!

1382
02:17:47,820 --> 02:17:50,664
Attention. Emergency.

1383
02:17:50,740 --> 02:17:53,903
All personnel must evacuate immediately.

1384
02:17:55,540 --> 02:17:58,669
Attention. Emergency.

1385
02:17:58,740 --> 02:18:03,268
All personnel must evacuate immediately.

1386
02:18:03,340 --> 02:18:05,786
You now have four minutes...

1387
02:18:05,860 --> 02:18:08,340
to reach minimum safe distance.

1388
02:18:24,300 --> 02:18:28,100
Come on, goddamn it!

1389
02:18:31,060 --> 02:18:33,870
Hold on to me!

1390
02:19:23,100 --> 02:19:25,910
Attention. Emergency.

1391
02:19:25,980 --> 02:19:29,905
All personnel must evacuate immediately.

1392
02:19:29,980 --> 02:19:32,665
You now have two minutes...

1393
02:19:32,740 --> 02:19:36,745
to reach minimum safe distance.

1394
02:19:42,460 --> 02:19:44,462
No.

1395
02:19:47,780 --> 02:19:50,670
Bishop, goddamn you!

1396
02:20:54,460 --> 02:20:56,542
Close your eyes, baby.

1397
02:20:59,100 --> 02:21:01,102
Look!

1398
02:21:07,980 --> 02:21:09,982
Come on! Come on!

1399
02:21:38,460 --> 02:21:41,066
Punch it, Bishop!

1400
02:22:26,260 --> 02:22:28,342
It's okay. We're okay.

1401
02:22:38,060 --> 02:22:40,028
Hey.

1402
02:22:41,420 --> 02:22:43,946
We made it.

1403
02:22:44,020 --> 02:22:46,022
I knew you'd come.

1404
02:23:00,940 --> 02:23:03,147
He's gonna be all right. He's just out.

1405
02:23:03,220 --> 02:23:05,587
I had to give him another shot for the pain.

1406
02:23:06,780 --> 02:23:09,386
We need a stretcher to carry him up to Medical.

1407
02:23:09,460 --> 02:23:11,462
Okay.

1408
02:23:17,140 --> 02:23:21,145
I'm sorry if I scared you. That platform was just becoming too unstable.

1409
02:23:21,220 --> 02:23:24,076
I had to circle and hope that things didn't get too rough to take you off.

1410
02:23:24,100 --> 02:23:28,071
Bishop, you did okay.

1411
02:23:28,140 --> 02:23:30,871
- I did? - Oh, yeah.

1412
02:24:10,300 --> 02:24:12,541
Go! Move!

1413
02:24:14,940 --> 02:24:18,103
No! Here! Here!

1414
02:24:18,220 --> 02:24:20,222
Run!

1415
02:24:25,500 --> 02:24:27,104
Here!

1416
02:25:55,820 --> 02:25:58,061
Get away from her, you bitch!

1417
02:26:19,180 --> 02:26:23,742
Come on! Come on!

1418
02:27:52,220 --> 02:27:54,666
Ripley!

1419
02:29:06,060 --> 02:29:08,540
Bishop!

1420
02:29:55,060 --> 02:29:58,064
- Mommy. - Oh, God!

1421
02:30:00,940 --> 02:30:04,149
Not bad for a h-human.

1422
02:30:51,260 --> 02:30:54,230
Are we gonna sleep all the way home?

1423
02:30:54,340 --> 02:30:57,344
- All the way home. - Can I dream?

1424
02:30:59,660 --> 02:31:02,266
Yes, honey. I think we both can.

1425
02:31:10,500 --> 02:31:13,629
- Sleep tight. - Affirmative.

